+    sections: [
+      {
+        rank: 1,
+        title: "Café Hoppe — Spui's 1670 standard-bearer",
+        description:
+          "Pouring since 1670 beside the Spui book market: sand on the floorboards, barrels behind the bar, professors and publishers three-deep at the evening borrel hour. Hoppe is the brown café in its platonic form — order a vaasje (the correct small beer; large glasses warm and flatten, locals will explain) and a genever beside it. Friday evenings overflow gloriously onto the square. The adjacent proeflokaal side entrance keeps the older ritual room. Begin all Amsterdam drinking education precisely here.",
