+        title: "Brouwerij 't IJ & the modern counterweight — windmill pints",
+        description:
+          "Under the De Gooyer windmill, the brewery that launched Dutch craft: the tasting room's terrace pours Zatte tripels and IJwit beside ostrich-adorned labels (long story), benches communal, prices honest, eastern-docklands light golden at the right hour. It's the bicycle-distance reward ride from Centrum — canal-belt drinking's open-air counterargument. Tours run weekends; closing comes early (8 p.m. spirit). Continue the modern thread at Oedipus or Troost taprooms if the evening demands — Amsterdam's brewing present holds its own against the genever past.",
