+        rank: 1,
+        title: "Rijksmuseum — the Night Watch and the deep wings",
+        description:
+          "The national collection's cathedral: Rembrandt's Night Watch commanding its Gallery of Honour, Vermeers in contemplative rank, and — the connoisseur's secret — near-empty wings of delftware, dollhouses and Asian pavilion calm two floors from the scrum. Book timed tickets online always; enter at opening or after 3 p.m.; budget three hours minimum. The library reading room and the garden's free sculpture rotations extend the visit. Cycling through the building's passage (a functioning bike road!) remains the most Amsterdam museum feature in existence.",
