+        rank: 6,
+        title: "The maritime and resistance registers — NEMO's neighbors",
+        description:
+          "The eastern docklands cluster completes the city's story: the Scheepvaartmuseum's golden-age maritime swagger (replica East Indiaman moored outside, navigational instruments like jewelry), the Resistance Museum's unbearable moral inventories (how ordinary Dutch chose, 1940–45 — the children's annex devastates gently), and NEMO's green-copper hull for traveling families. Combination strategy: maritime morning, resistance afternoon sobering, NEMO rooftop's free city panorama restoring. The IJ ferry connections make Noord's art hangars (NDSM) the optional modern coda.",
