+        title: "Bloemenmarkt — the floating market, decoded",
+        description:
+          "The Singel's famous flower market floats on houseboats as it has since 1862 — now candidly split between tourist bulb-bins and genuine stalls. Use it correctly: morning hours for actual cut flowers (peonies in May, dahlias late summer) before coach crowds; certified bulbs with import stamps if carrying home (US/AU customs care); the photogenic tulip bunches in season cost less than postcards claim. The real charm is structural — buying ranunculus over water, church bells timing the wrap. Exit via the Munttoren end for canal-ring continuation.",
+      },
+      {
+        rank: 2,
+        title: "Tulip season — Keukenhof and the bulb fields",
+        description:
+          "Mid-March to mid-May, the country performs its color anthem: Keukenhof's seven million bulbs orchestrated through woodland gardens (book timed entry; weekday mornings essential; the gardens absorb crowds better than the bus logistics suggest), and — the freer version — bulb-field cycling routes around Lisse and the Noordoostpolder where stripes of saturation run to the horizon. Field etiquette is real: photograph from paths, never enter rows (growers' livelihoods, drone-enforced increasingly). Peak bloom hits mid-April typically; the season's lottery is half the romance.",
+      },
+      {
+        rank: 3,
+        title: "Neighborhood bloemenwinkels — the daily ritual",
+        description:
+          "The city's true flower culture is domestic: corner florists in the Jordaan and De Pijp wrapping Friday bouquets for canal-house tables — seasonal Dutch-grown stems, prices democratic, wrapping ceremonious. Gerda's on Runstraat earned its fame (florist-to-the-stylish since decades back); the Noordermarkt Saturday stalls and Albert Cuyp's flower rows serve the people's tier. Participate: hotel rooms deserve tulips too, and ten euros buys the city's mood. The vase-light through canal windows at dusk explains the entire Dutch still-life tradition.",
+      },
+      {
+        rank: 4,
