+        title: "U Fleků — the 1499 institution, eyes open",
+        description:
+          "Brewing on-site since 1499 — possibly the world's oldest continuously operating brewpub — U Fleků serves exactly one beer: the famous dark 13° Flekovský ležák, malty-coffee depth, delivered to communal tables by waiters in perpetual orbit. The rules of engagement: beers land unbidden (a nod accepts; cover your glass to cease), the Becherovka tray circling is NOT complimentary (decline clearly unless wanted), accordion serenades expect coins. It's touristy, theatrical and genuinely historic simultaneously — go knowing the game, drink the dark, enjoy the circus once.",
