+        description:
+          "The Ambiente group's long hall rebuilt Czech pub culture's confidence: unpasteurized Pilsner Urquell from horizontal tanks (tankovna — brewery-fresh, never bottled), poured by trained výčepní in the three canonical styles — hladinka (creamy standard), šnyt (half beer, generous foam, the 'I'm pacing' order), mlíko ('milk' — nearly all foam, dessert-soft, downed while foam-sweet). Order each across an evening for the full education. Svíčková and fried cheese support from the kitchen. Reserve evenings; lunch walks in. This is modern Prague's benchmark pour.",
