+          "The Old Town's most defended literary pub: writer Bohumil Hrabal held court here for decades (Havel famously brought Bill Clinton in 1994 to show him 'where real Czechs drink'), and the regulars' tables still operate on seniority law. Pilsner only, conversation Czech, seats scarce after 4 p.m. — arrive at the 3 p.m. opening, accept shared-table diplomacy, order by raised finger, and absorb the tobacco-varnished gravity. Not a performance for visitors; a working institution tolerating them. The discomfort is the authenticity certificate.",
