+        title: "Vinohradský pivovar & the neighborhood renaissance",
+        description:
+          "The craft-era counterargument lives in Vinohrady: the neighborhood brewery's tied house pours its own unfiltered 11° and specials to a local crowd of families, freelancers and beer pilgrims — no Old Town surcharge, no accordion. The wider new wave (Dva kohouti's Karlín taproom energy, Pivovar Matuška's hoppy revolution available citywide) proves Czech brewing's future matches its past. Saturday afternoons here — beer garden tables, dogs underfoot, trams rattling past — deliver the lived Prague the postcards crop out. Cash useful; reservations unnecessary.",
