+          "Svíčková na smetaně — beef sirloin under root-vegetable cream sauce, bread dumplings (knedlíky) deployed as sauce-transport, cranberries and lemon-cream negotiating richness — is the dish Czech grandmothers are judged by. Benchmark versions: Lokál's calibrated classic, Café Savoy's elegant take, and any Vinohrady hospoda where the lunch crowd runs Czech. The dumpling protocol: they're for dragging, not buttering. Paired with a šnyt pour, it's the complete Czech argument — order it first meal, calibrate everything after.",
