+          "The 1893 grand café restored to neo-Renaissance ceiling glory: Czech-French breakfasts (the 'Savoy' spread with eggs, ham, fresh-baked vánočka), legendary větrník choux from the in-house patisserie, and white-aproned service running Viennese precision at Prague prices. Weekend brunch queues form — book ahead or weekday it. The Malá Strana location serves Petřín-and-castle itineraries perfectly. It's the dress-slightly-up morning institution: monarchy-era atmosphere, kolache-to-champagne range, and the pastry counter's gravitational pull on departure.",
