+          "The world's largest ancient castle rewards selective ambition: St. Vitus Cathedral's Gothic verticality (Mucha's art-nouveau window, the silver tomb's baroque excess) headlines; Old Royal Palace's Vladislav Hall and the Defenestration window supply the history-pivot anecdote; Golden Lane's miniature houses (Kafka wrote at No. 22) charm efficiently. Strategy: circuit-B ticketing covers essentials; first-entry timing (9 a.m.) or post-15:00 thins the tide; the cathedral's nave is free-entry while choir access tickets. Descend via Malá Strana's gardens, never the tour-bus route.",
